The paper proposes a new model class for solving fundamental tasks that neural ordinary differential equation models cannot solve. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with dynamic vector field selection, which suggests that it may belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with trajectory paths, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper demonstrates the model's ability to capture the natural dynamics of human behavior, which suggests that it may belong to the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
